<Review>We ordered our food, 3 burgers 1 fry, at 1:55pm. The cashier immediately flipped the screen around and asked for a tip. For what? For taking our order? Do they not get paid? I mean, I understand tipping at a restaurant where you are seated, drinks are brought out to you, you know? Service? But what am I tipping for? Do gas pumps ask for a tip? Does the walmart cashier ask for a tip? Does In-N-Out ask for a tip? I am all for tipping, but immediately after you place your order?
The place was not busy at all, there were no orders ahead of us. One guy was working the grill while the cashier dude was on his cell phone. 20 minutes later at 2:15 I walked up and asked if everything was okay, the cashier guy said that a big "Uber Eats" order came in and those have priority and that our food would be out shortly.
I don't mind spending $4.75 on a burger, but by no means was what we received $4.75 burgers. They were not even warm, asked for "no catsup" came with catsup anyway. And I was not expecting the "Little Big Burger" to be quite as "Little" as it was.
I cant imagine a place like this staying in business for long. I'm sure enough people's curiosity has kept a steady flow of customers up until this point, but with prices, product, and service at the level of what I experienced, I doubt they get many return visitors.

Edit: I guess I was right. "Permanently Closed". ü§∑‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è</Review><Response>None</Response><Name>Jesse B</Name><GmapID>0x80d959ceaaaaaaab:0xeb37070f5642b02a</GmapID><user>104391482514180957365</user><rating>1< /rating></record>

<username>Alyssa Elkins< /username><text>The first time visiting Little Big Burger I was attracted by how you can see the person cooking your food like how In and Out does. The staff is super friendly and helped me figure out what kind of burger I wanted by saying how they cook their burgers to what condiments you want on it. The price may be expensive to some, but their quality for their burgers and fries are amazing so much better than big burgers at fast food restaurants. <time>1523047572354< /time><gmap_id>0x80d959ceaaaaaaab:0xeb37070f5642b02a<//gmap_id><rate>3<//rate><Resp>None<//Resp><pictures>None</pictures>< review>
Very tasty, truffle fries are unique. BUT watch for chili pepper in the ketchup they put on their burgers. I have a family member who has serious allergic reactions to pepper in general (systemic, not sneezing). This same ketchup is apparently also served at their tables and also mixed into their fry sauce. For most people this isn't going to be a problem but if it is then watch out.
I'll go back but it will have to be on my own.
Three stars for really tasty food but a ruined afternoon over ketchup that I only realized contained chili pepper after examining the bottles at the tables.<//review>

< Review>
You can tell the burgers were probably hand formed pattied and they did taste fresh. The buns were very greasy, however, and their fries are overpriced and overhyped. When they opened, they had a guy offering samples of their truffle fries, which are the obly fries featured on the menu- and they were good at that point. Having actually paid money for them the second time, I felt like they were normal fries and they weren't worth the cost.
Also, my partner had asked for bacon on his burger, and I didn't, but they ended up putting it on both anyway. And I know what you're thinking- why complain about bacon? It was dry and pretty much overcooked and it ruined the texture of the burger. So there's that.<//Review>

<pictures>None</pictures>< review>
My first visit to Brickhouse was years ago, but it is still a vivid picture in my mind. I was greeted warmly by the owner, Barbara and others that were assisting her. We enjoyed some home-cooked Southern cuisine and beverages, including wine, and enjoyed a night of scheduled activities throughout the Chitlin Circuit series. I have been on several occasions, including the series, and each time there was beautiful art work to take in from local artists and inspiring, thought-provoking words shared by the talented poets that graced the mic. All are welcomed. Love flows freely to and through each person that walks through the door. The atmosphere is wonderful.</review>

<date>1576631057460<//date><rating>5<//rating><review>99 cent tacos. For dollar tacos, these are a great value and tasty. I tried 4 tacos here and the staff were also cheerful and welcoming.
1.Chorizo- my favorite of the four. Crispy and soft chorizo. A mild to medium spiciness. Packed with flavor and needs no salsa.
2. Carnitas- Crispy traditional pork carnitas that go well with salsa verde.
3. Asada- Ok for the price but a little drier and lacked strong marinated flavor. For 99 cents, its still a good deal.
4. Pollo- Not dry and nicely flavoured.  Also great with salsa verde or roja.

< Review>
I like their designs and their quality is good. I own four of their pieces currently. Their service on the other hand has been very disappointing. I‚Äôm still waiting for one item which has been back ordered for a long time. They have given me several estimated dates of delivery that have come and gone maybe 5-6 times most without notice or a call from them. I‚Äôve been told ‚Äúit‚Äôs in the port‚Äù and waiting to be unloaded and then later been told ‚Äúit‚Äôs on the ship.‚Äù I‚Äôm approaching 4 months since my pre-paid order. When I politely asked for a discount given all the delays, I was told they would have to contact their manager. No one followed up with me as usual. When I called back after the next estimated delivery passed, I was told the manager said they would Not offer a discount because they had done nothing wrong. If poor service and constantly missed delivery times with little outreach or notifications is doing your job well, I guess they are right. This will likely be my last piece bought from Scandinavian Designs.

Update: Shortly after posting this review I got an email from a manager who offered me their floor model or a small discount on my order which was a nice gesture. It would have been great if the service happened earlier but I appreciate the effort to make the situation better so I gave them an extra star. In the end, our piece arrived after about four months of waiting and we do love it.< /Review>

< Review>
I have been a resident for 11 years.  A month after my arrival, Zero stars.  With the multiplicity of managers, I think the owners have finally found a person with the management skills and demeanor to handle a diverse demographic with its fair share of residents and some  who are just ornery.
It will take time to get resident behavior to accept rules agreed to at signing of lease.
The only problem I forsee is finding a person to complement our remaining maintenance person.  Most have had rudimentary housekeeping experience with no supplemental skills as the employee who just left.  Only 3 capable personnel in 11 years now just 1.  All in all, as a senior approaching 80, Hayward Village Senior Apartments is clean, quiet and restfull.  What more does a senior need other than good health and longevity.  If you are a nice person and not prone to find fault with every little thing then apply.< /Review>

<Review>The service was great, we ordered to go and ate on the patio with our small dog. They waited to make our dessert until we were ready. It was clean and nice outside.

This wasy first time back to a Bob's Big Boy in like 15 years. I anticipated the chili spaghetti and was excited to share the experience with our kids. While the noodles were perfectly cooked, everything tasted really bland.

I was surprised when one of my kids, a picky eater, said the french fry he tried was bad. I grabbed it to see what he was talking about and took a bite of his rejection.

< Name>
Irene Leung</Name>
< pictures>
[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipOZ76GDPxFTVcmGwW-3wuk7Y0HhVwxyPUR_kPlB=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]< /pictures>
<text>After a few months of Stay At Home, I decided to venture out to the Bob's Big Boy in Norco.   I am fan of Big Boy's Hamburger since I was about 5 - 6 years old.     I was born and raised in Pasadena.  My parents would go to the Bob's Big Boy on Colorado.  We either ate in the small take out patio or took the burgers home.   Pasadena did have 3 Bob's Big Boy.     Two on Colorado Blvd. and 1 on Lake Ave.   I do miss them.  Even the ones in Barstow, CA are closed now.  There is only 3 left here.  The original in Burbank, CA, Downey, CA and Norco, CA.

We drove down to Norco for lunch.   I called ahead to make sure they have dine-in service.  They do have dine-in service.  We were greeted by the host and seated right away.  The waitress was very courteous, attentive and very friendly.

She took our drink orders and we were ready to order.  I had their Big Boy combo (regular size) not the jumbo size one.

Salad was fresh.  The burger came with fries.   I truly enjoyed the Big Boy hamburger.  It's been a while since I ate one too.

The server kept on coming back making sure drinks were filled and making sure we were happy with food.

I would recommend this place.   Very close to the freeway too.

I would go back to Bob's Big Boy again.< /text>< Rate>
5</Rate>

1561518245394</Time>
<Rating>3<//Rating>< Review>
Okay. Now this place is iconic in SoCal and I haven't been to a big boy in close to 30 years. I saw a sign off the 15 freeway and said..Dang! Gotta stop and get a burger. I did and well it was much better in memory than it was today. The burger was similar to the big mac, when I was hoping for something different and was missing the seasoning. I know I know salt is bad... but my gosh it's good on meet when cooking. So basically it was missing the taste I was hoping for from my childhood memory. The fries were great as was the salad with Bob's ranch dressing.  The service from the folks working was fantastic and the restaurant itself was classic old time comfort.  I will be back to try something else on the menu as I saw a number of items that looked good. I will update one I try something else.</Review>

<Rate>2</Rate>< text>
The service was on par for a restaurant. We showed up late morning and they offered a breakfast buffet. We opted to order from the menu to get something a bit more fresh. Scrambled eggs, hash browns, pancakes, french toast, etc. My scrambled eggs were undercooked and the pancakes were reheated in the microwave, you can tell because dough gets a rubber consistency when it's overly reheated in the microwave. The hash browns were super greasy. Nice people, but I don't think we'll be back.<//text>

I was served two pancakes that were about an 1/8" thick, really I mean wafer thin! They tasted like they were cooked on a dirty grill. To my surprise, I was charged $7.00 for said pancakes. Apparently when Marie callender's closed their restaurant in Corona Bob's big boy Norco figures that they can slack and they won't lose any business to the competition little did they know but Bob's big boy Norco is losing business. We have ordered the same takeout dinners from this restaurant a few times and tonight it got to the point where I just had to post a review on Yelp and now on Google. <UserId.>100355377334831342691< /UserId.><rate>5< /rate><name>Karen Mahan< /name><review>I've been coming to Bob's Big Boy since I was a small kid and we still make special trips out of our way to eat here. This is my favorite burger (sorry In-n-Out!)  I have ONLY had the Big Boy Classic Burger and their Fudge Cake dessert...EVER, so can't attest to their other food offerings, but they have a small salad bar and a large menu. You can get your drinks made with Vanilla or Cherry. They serve Pepsi products unfortunately...sad.
I just know this is comfort food for me! They have a 50's vibe inside with booths and tables in red, white and blue decor.   Service is fast and great most of the time.  They sometimes have Car Shows in there large parking lot.  There is a " Malt and Ice Cream Shoppe" inside the restaurant with a small gift shop selling cookies, candy T-Shirts and gifts.  This is "Americana" modernized!
Did you know that the Bob's Big Boy statue which stands outside the Norco restaurant, is the only one to have their " Bob's mascot" altered? They received special permission to add the cowboy hat on Bob!  Norco is "Horsetown USA" where the horses outnumber the people.<//review></record>

<text>In ancient times, Bob's Big Boy restaurants herds roamed the plains in abundance.
Then came the dark times when evil corporations ran the chain into the ground.
Today there are few remaining Bob's Big Boys left in the wild. The iconic Big Boy combo with the Bleu Cheese dressing of my childhood is now a rarity as stores in Diamond Bar close.  There are only a handful of stores left. This store was not crowded on a Saturday night, which makes me worry about its future. I'm sure the original Toluca Lake store will be around forever...but please people, visit all the stores so that you and your progeny can experience an American classic.<//text>< Pics>

<name>Rob Titus<//name>< Review>
In ancient times, Bob's Big Boy restaurants herds roamed the plains in abundance.
Then came the dark times when evil corporations ran the chain into the ground.
Today there are few remaining Bob's Big Boys left in the wild. The iconic Big Boy combo with the Bleu Cheese dressing of my childhood is now a rarity as stores in Diamond Bar close.  There are only a handful of stores left. This store was not crowded on a Saturday night, which makes me worry about its future. I'm sure the original Toluca Lake store will be around forever...but please people, visit all the stores so that you and your progeny can experience an American classic.< /Review>
